CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 2, 1974, pg. 15 reads: "Talented - Whether it is the Neighborhood Block Club, Family Re-union, Church Rally or the "Wax Fax," to which she contributed during her stint in the Women's Army Corp, Mrs. Alice Charles Suber, 7230 Kedron St., has shown unique talent for writing, poetry, dramatic skits and prose. She also takes the responsibility of posting any news about Wesley Center Members of the "Spotlight Bulletin Board" in the church vestry. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Alice Charles Suber wearing shirt with abstract print, seated at desk, possibly in Wesley Center AME Zion Church
